Simple Remote Shell C++

Author:		 	Adrian Murillo
Date: 			2/14/2021

Contents: 
	lab_3
	├── Makefile					- Makefile. Use "make" to compile
	├── README
	├── bin
	│   ├── myclient				- client program executable
	│   ├── myserver				- server program executable
	│   ├── shell_client.o 	
	│   ├── shell_server.o
	│   └── util.o
	├── doc
	│   └── Remote_Shell_C++.pdf	- documentation of the project
	└── src
	    ├── shell_client.cpp		- client c++ implementation
	    ├── shell_client.h			- client libraries and parameters
	    ├── shell_server.cpp		- server c++ implementation
	    ├── shell_server.h			- server libraries and parameters
	    ├── unp.h					- Unix Network Programming library
	    ├── util.cpp				- utility c++ functions - err_sys()
	    └── util.h					- utility libraries and parameters

	3 directories, 15 files

Description:

Server and client implementation of a simple remote shell application. The user of the client 
application can type various Unix shell commands, which execute on the server and return re-
sults back to the client. 
